Session Summary (2026-04-19)

Researched Remotion — evaluated whether the JS/React video-generation framework had any fit in this pipeline. Verdict: it solves the opposite problem (generating video from code, not processing existing footage). Filed as a long-term idea for branded titles/lower thirds only, not relevant to current work.

Built per-segment subject hint system — lets you tell the tracker which band member to follow, per scene, using plain color descriptions like yellow shirt. Full implementation across 5 files + 1 new shared utility:

tools/color_utils.py (new) — color matching engine. NAMED_COLORS table (yellow, orange, red, green, cyan, blue, purple, pink, white, black) maps to HSV ranges. score_color() samples the torso region of a bounding box and returns a 0–1 match score. pick_by_hint() selects the best-matching candidate from all detections.

tools/detect_mediapipe.py — now returns up to N detected people per frame (not just 1). Default cap: 3 (the band), configurable up to 5, or unlimited via --all-subjects. Annotation structure changed from (all_boxes, selected_box, mode) to (all_boxes, selected_idx, mode). Color hint applied at detection time.

tools/detect_yolo.py — same multi-subject + hint pattern for the Haar/YOLO fallback path.

tools/track_subject.py — subject_hint, max_subjects, all_subjects threaded through _detect_frames → detect_crop_trajectory → write_tracked_vertical. Debug video now draws non-tracked people as gray boxes labeled P1, P2, P3.

tools/plan_video.py — added --max-subjects (default 3, max 5) and --all-subjects flags. Debug video now shows all detected people with P-labels so you can identify who's who before filling in subject_focus.

tools/cut_clips.py — added --planning-csv, --max-subjects, --all-subjects flags. Loads the planning CSV and maps each clip's time range to the dominant planning segment by overlap, pulling subject_focus as the color hint passed to tracking.

Also shipped: README.md (project overview, current + future workflow, version history table) and committed v4/v5/v6 session notes.

Where to pick up next: Run plan_video.py with --all-subjects on real show footage, verify all 3 band members appear as labeled boxes in the debug video, then test a color-hinted cut with --planning-csv



